SQLMap 

1. Overview
What SQLMap is
Automated SQLi detection & exploitation
Databases supported
When to use it

---

2. Installation
Linux: preinstalled

Manual git clone

Windows zip package

---

3. Key Features

DB fingerprinting
Dumping tables
OS shell
File read/write
Automatic payload tampering

----

4. Important Parameters

Include LOTS of parameters (since SQLMap is huge):
Target Input
-u
-r (request file)
-g (google dork)
Testing Level
--level=1-5
--risk=1-3
Technique Selection
--technique=BEUSTQ
Detection
--batch
--fresh-queries
Enumeration
--dbs
--tables
--columns
--dump
--dump-all
Authentication
--cookie
--auth-type
--auth-cred
Bypass WAF
--tamper=space2comment
--random-agent
OS Interaction
--os-shell
--os-cmd

---

5. Usage Examples
sqlmap -u "https://site.com?id=1" --dbs
sqlmap -r req.txt --dump
sqlmap -u URL --risk=3 --level=5 --tamper=space2comment

----


6. Real Attack Examples

Extracting admin table
Reading /etc/passwd

Getting command shell
